<font FACE="Arial Black" SIZE="7" COLOR="#000000">

<p align="center"></font><font FACE="Arial Black" COLOR="#000000" size="6">A comparison of conventional hypermedia system with the new model</font></p>

<p>&nbsp;<font FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="7" COLOR="#000000">

<ul>
  <li><font FACE="Times New Roman" COLOR="#000000" size="6">In previous models, all operations are carried out by an active central unit which exerts control on a set of passive components
</font></li>
  <li><font FACE="Times New Roman" COLOR="#000000" size="6">In this model, no main resource responsible for the global management 
</font></li>
  <li><font FACE="Times New Roman" COLOR="#000000" size="6">In this model, an aggregation of autonomous and independent actors
</font></li>
  <li><font FACE="Times New Roman" COLOR="#000000" size="6">In this model, each actor has a behavioral responsibility and a partial perception of the other members of the community</font></li>
</ul>
</font>
